cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision tasks and deep features extracted from pre-trained Convolutional Neural Networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for computing the activeness of neurons and network connections, which involves training a neural network in a top-down manner. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could place it in the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
